exports[`mangadex — live snapshots > search: The Ancient Magus' Bride 1`] = `
[
  {
    "author": "Yamazaki Kore",
    "cover_url": "https://uploads.mangadex.org/covers/195023bf-cf9a-4772-94ef-09dd6eddea84/2247a839-758e-4fd5-b179-cbea596044fb.jpg.256.jpg",
    "description": "With her mother dead and father long gone, Chise Hatori has spent her childhood being passed unwanted from relative to relative, 
until she finally makes her unfortunate way to a strange and improbable auction block.

Offered as a “Slay Vega” to the highest bidder, Chise is purchased by the (literally) boneheaded Elias Ainsworth, 
who promises to take her on as his apprentice.

Elias is a mage, and his world is one of dragons and faeries - but before Chise can begin to get accustomed to all of this, 
Elias drops another bombshell. Apparently Chise isn't just intended to be his apprentice - she will also be his bride.",
    "id": "195023bf-cf9a-4772-94ef-09dd6eddea84",
    "status": "ongoing",
    "tags": "Monsters, Demons, Ghosts, Romance, Magic, Drama, School Life, Fantasy, Monster Girls, Slice of Life, Supernatural",
    "title": "The Ancient Magus' Bride",
    "year": 2013,
  },
  {
    "author": "Yamazaki Kore",
    "cover_url": "https://uploads.mangadex.org/covers/34a09d2f-fc71-446f-9092-c48eb8b2f811/dcb85cec-7602-4b4a-be6f-4eb428abcf46.jpg.256.jpg",
    "description": "**The Annotated Magus**

Fans of The Ancient Magus’ Bride are sure to love this in-depth guide to its story. Chapter-by-chapter notes provide insight into the author’s intent and the world of the story, covering mythology, magic, and more. This handbook contains spoilers aplenty, and is meant to enhance the reading experience for the first three volumes of the series. If you’re hoping for a deeper examination of the story of Elias and Chise, look no further!",
    "id": "34a09d2f-fc71-446f-9092-c48eb8b2f811",
    "status": "ongoing",
    "tags": null,
    "title": "The Ancient Magus’ Bride Supplement",
    "year": 2017,
  },
  {
    "author": "Yamazaki Kore",
    "cover_url": "https://uploads.mangadex.org/covers/d9feca8f-492a-403a-810e-0a434fd8539c/f40a5397-5e9e-42de-b7af-b8b0872c6070.jpg.256.jpg",
    "description": "An orphaned boy named Blue is taken under the wing of the magus Gisele to explore the artistry of magic in Paris. For readers interested in a gender-swapped take on the original premise of The Ancient Magus’ Bride, this beautifully illustrated manga is full of all-new wonder.",
    "id": "d9feca8f-492a-403a-810e-0a434fd8539c",
    "status": "completed",
    "tags": "Magic, Fantasy, Supernatural",
    "title": "Mahoutsukai no Yome Shihen.108 - Majutsushi no Ao",
    "year": 2019,
  },
  {
    "author": "Godai Yuu",
    "cover_url": "https://uploads.mangadex.org/covers/1551da93-c715-43ac-ad0f-7d682eafdfae/b061b417-3261-4288-a357-1441369c1ac3.jpg.256.jpg",
    "description": "**Changelings in the Big Apple**  
  
Faerie-born Jack Flash and her half-wolf brother Larry run a detective agency in New York City specializing in crimes committed in the hazy boundary between the human and faerie realms. They never expected to receive a letter from an ancient magus of the Old World, but Echos, caretaker of dragons, has a task for them.   
An all-new [Ancient Magus’ Bride](https://mangadex.org/manga/10801) spin-off series!",
    "id": "1551da93-c715-43ac-ad0f-7d682eafdfae",
    "status": "ongoing",
    "tags": "Adventure, Magic, Fantasy, Supernatural",
    "title": "Mahoutsukai no Yome Shihen.75 - Inazuma Jack to Yousei Jiken",
    "year": 2019,
  },
  {
    "author": "Gajang",
    "cover_url": "https://uploads.mangadex.org/covers/bae862e5-6155-412e-a1f2-10877687a057/1d6115d4-2d91-4cbc-af21-45fe2ce616d5.jpg.256.jpg",
    "description": "Waking up in a fantasy novel set in an ancient magical world was confusing enough for Sisha. But on top of that, she happens to be the only person who could read and understand the old texts recovered from the secret library kept hidden for thousands of years... Furthermore, to Sisha's surprise, the ancient language of forbidden magic turned out to be none other than modern English! With the emperor now praising her ability to decipher the words of Alphabet, Sisha steps up from a mere sidekick to an incredible main lead--in a world where whatever she speaks in her mother tongue is a key to unlock the powerful magic.",
    "id": "bae862e5-6155-412e-a1f2-10877687a057",
    "status": "completed",
    "tags": "Long Strip, Romance, Comedy, Drama, Fantasy, Full Color",
    "title": "Only I Can Speak the Ancient Language of Magic",
    "year": 2023,
  },
  {
    "author": "Satou Tsutomu",
    "cover_url": "https://uploads.mangadex.org/covers/d1874a5b-9397-41ee-9289-415e975b53bd/d809e2ed-78f6-4261-befe-74e020723201.jpg.256.jpg",
    "description": "Zhou Gongjin, who was the mastermind of what happened in the Parasite Doll incident of Nine Schools Competition, has fled from Yokohama to the area of the original ancient magic users group centred around Kyoto also known as the *traditionalists*.   
Since then two months have passed and the National High School Magic Thesis Competition will soon be held again. This year's Thesis Competition is being held in Kyoto sponsored by the Magic Association and in their conference hall.   
Tatsuya gets visited by the Kuroba twins who as representatives bring Yotsuba Maya's letter to him. The letter is a request from his aunt saying "I hope for your cooperation to capture Zhou Gongjin".  
While it is questionable that whether it is a "command" rather than a "request", Tatsuya and Miyuki go to Kudou's house as they are in the centre as opponents of the traditionalists. As a result, the two siblings have a fated encounter with the "Genius Augmented Magician”.   
Conspiracy of the ancient city was the stage. The fate that has continued to smoulder away in the back of the history of magician development, Tatsuya and Miyuki and his companions are challenged.   
  
Adaptation of the original novel's volumes 14-15.",
    "id": "d1874a5b-9397-41ee-9289-415e975b53bd",
    "status": "completed",
    "tags": "Sci-Fi, Action, Romance, Comedy, Magic, Harem, Military, Drama, School Life, Supernatural, Adaptation",
    "title": "Mahouka Koukou no Rettousei - Koto Nairan-hen",
    "year": 2019,
  },
  {
    "author": "Snap Studio (三原社)",
    "cover_url": "https://uploads.mangadex.org/covers/bf4686ec-aac8-4b83-8242-8a4c01241979/ca6a1396-ac8e-4f5e-b95c-62bc9bd1daf8.jpg.256.jpg",
    "description": "After CEO Qi's death, he crossed over to a different world. He originally thought that he was a savior, only when he got dressed up and sent to the wedding bed, did he realise that he became the bride for the devil! When faced with a frivolous and doting devil, when exactly can the cold and aloof CEO give birth?!

---
After being murdered, the CEO of Qi's Group travels to an otherworldly land and becomes its Savior. The only way to save the world is to become the wife of the God of Desire and awaken the power of new life with him?!

---
**Original Web Comic:** [AC.QQ](https://ac.qq.com/Comic/comicInfo/id/649185), [BiliBili Manhua](https://manga.bilibili.com/detail/mc30514), [IQIYI](https://www.iqiyi.com/manhua/detail_1aedr7uj5bp.html), [KuaiKan Manhua](https://www.kuaikanmanhua.com/web/topic/8386)

**Official English Translations:** [INKR Comics](https://inkr.com/ik-title-688), [WebComics](http://www.webcomicsapp.com/comic/612dda758c252b0ce439d134)",
    "id": "bf4686ec-aac8-4b83-8242-8a4c01241979",
    "status": "completed",
    "tags": "Romance, Comedy, Boys' Love, Fantasy, Web Comic",
    "title": "Devil's Lover",
    "year": 2020,
  },
]
`;

